{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://tintaliquida.github.io/narratingwaterscapes/manifests/history-of-the-r-o-indio-project.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"en":["History of the Río Indio Project"]},"homepage":[{"id":"https://tintaliquida.github.io/narratingwaterscapes","type":"Text","label":{"en":["History of the Río Indio Project"]},"format":"text/html"}],"metadata":[{"label":{"en":["Description"]},"value":{"en":["Since the 1930s, the idea of ​​harnessing the potential of the Indio River as a water source for the country and for the Canal has been under consideration."]}},{"label":{"en":["Language"]},"value":{"en":["English"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://tintaliquida.github.io/narratingwaterscapes/history_of_the_río_indio_project/canvas/7","type":"Canvas","duration":0,"annotations":[{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://tintaliquida.github.io/narratingwaterscapes/manifests/history_of_the_río_indio_project-canvas7-1","type":"AnnotationPage","label":{"en":["Default"]},"items":[{"@context":"http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld","type":"Annotation","motivation":["commenting","tagging"],"id":"https://tintaliquida.github.io/narratingwaterscapes/history_of_the_río_indio_project/canvas/7/page1","body":[{"type":"TextualBody","value":"Whereas the documentary 'Familia' (2007) presents Rio Indio through the moment local communities encounter maps, measurements, and uncertainty, the ACP chronology narrates the same project as a decades-long sequence of technical studies.","format":"text/plain","motivation":"commenting"},{"type":"TextualBody","value":"state mapping","format":"text/plain","purpose":"tagging","motivation":"tagging"},{"type":"TextualBody","value":"dam","format":"text/plain","purpose":"tagging","motivation":"tagging"},{"type":"TextualBody","value":"reservoir","format":"text/plain","purpose":"tagging","motivation":"tagging"}],"target":"https://tintaliquida.github.io/narratingwaterscapes/history_of_the_río_indio_project/canvas/7#t=0,6"},{"@context":"http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld","type":"Annotation","motivation":["commenting","tagging"],"id":"https://tintaliquida.github.io/narratingwaterscapes/history_of_the_río_indio_project/canvas/7/page1","body":[{"type":"TextualBody","value":"Across eight chapters spanning the 1930s to the present, the reservoir appears as the gradual outcome of hydrological planning. The comparison shows how the same infrastructure can be narrated either as a disruptive territorial reorganization or as administrative continuity.","format":"text/plain","motivation":"commenting"},{"type":"TextualBody","value":"state mapping","format":"text/plain","purpose":"tagging","motivation":"tagging"},{"type":"TextualBody","value":"dam","format":"text/plain","purpose":"tagging","motivation":"tagging"},{"type":"TextualBody","value":"reservoir","format":"text/plain","purpose":"tagging","motivation":"tagging"}],"target":"https://tintaliquida.github.io/narratingwaterscapes/history_of_the_río_indio_project/canvas/7#t=7,235"}]}],"items":[{"id":"https://tintaliquida.github.io/narratingwaterscapes/history_of_the_río_indio_project-canvas7/paintings","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://tintaliquida.github.io/narratingwaterscapes/history_of_the_río_indio_project-canvas7/paintings","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","body":{"id":"https://youtu.be/ZcmKNspvtvQ?si=2mbkoB8ZddvxbsZp","type":"Video","format":"unknown","duration":0},"target":"https://tintaliquida.github.io/narratingwaterscapes/history_of_the_río_indio_project/canvas/7"}]}]}]}